Installing Docker

Install the Docker prerequisites:
#sudo yum install -y yum-utils device-mapper-persistent-data lvm2

Using yum-config-manager, add the CentOS-specific Docker repo:
#sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo

Install Docker:
#sudo yum -y install docker-ce

Add user account to interact with docker daemon 
#sudo usermod -aG docker cloud_user

exit and login as the user again.

check docker version and pull image from docker repository

e.g docker run hello-world

